class Solution {
public:
    string answerString(string word, int numFriends) {
        int n = word.size();
        if (numFriends == 1) return word;
        int len = n - numFriends + 1;
        string best = "";
        for (int i = 0; i + len <= n; ++i) {
            string cur = word.substr(i, len);
            if (cur > best) best = cur;
        }
        return best;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n^2)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The lexicographically largest substring that can appear in any split is always the maximum length-(n-k+1) substring of the original word, because any split must leave one part of at least that length.

